snippet: Two gauges of stock values — the cyclically adjusted price-earnings ratio, or Cape, and a gauge called the Q, which was devised by the economist James Tobin — show that stocks today are expensive by historical measures.
lead_paragraph: Two gauges of stock values — the cyclically adjusted price-earnings ratio, or Cape, and a gauge called the Q, which was devised by the economist James Tobin — show that stocks today are expensive by historical measures.
